  "text": "This study has further demonstrated the potential to use information from several European clinical databases for paediatric research, as proposed by Neubert et al. [CITATION_1] . We have shown that routine clinical databases can be used to monitor the prevalence of diabetes. Despite the differences in prevalences which we observed and in line with previously published data, at least in children insulin prescribing is a good surrogate for type 1 diabetes [CITATION_2] . The results of the present study clearly demonstrate that it would be feasible to utilize these databases as an automated system to study the prevalence of type 1 diabetes in children.",
